n & Management","homepage_url":"https://kmesh.net","id":"orchestration-management--service-mesh--kmesh","logo":"logos/7a6797f45399b0a78b94d7cafdde473862b600264e2fb52aa297d42cbc62c2d8.svg","name":"Kmesh","subcategory":"Service Mesh","website":"https://kmesh.net","accepted_at":"2024-10-17","artwork_url":"https://github.com/cncf/artwork/tree/master/projects/kmesh","chat_channel":"#kmesh","clomonitor_name":"kmesh","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","description":"Kmesh is a high-performance and low overhead service mesh data plane based on eBPF and programmable kernel. Kmesh brings traffic management, security and monitoring to service communication without needing application code changes. It is natively sidecarless, zero intrusion and without adding any resource cost to application container.","devstats_url":"https://kmesh.devstats.cncf.io/","lfx_slug":"kmesh","maturity":"sandbox","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/kmesh-net/kmesh","primary":true}],"slack_url":"https://slack.cncf.io/","tag":["network"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/Kmesh_net","youtube_url":"https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC-ToQ9h0SR_w492PpIfZAGw"},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","homepage_url":"https://kuma.io","id":"orchestration-management--service-mesh--kuma","logo":"logos/0da973ff2e1bf921136027a4ea3ff8bbc78a984652119fe23ffadebe7c8b7a33.svg","name":"Kuma","subcategory":"Service Mesh","website":"https://kuma.io","accepted_at":"2020-06-25","artwork_url":"https://github.com/cncf/artwork/tree/master/projects/kuma","blog_url":"https://kuma.io/blog/","clomonitor_name":"kuma","crunchbase_url":"https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/cloud-native-computing-foundation","devstats_url":"https://kuma.devstats.cncf.io/","lfx_slug":"kuma","maturity":"sandbox","latest_annual_review_at":"2023-06-10","latest_annual_review_url":"https://github.com/cncf/toc/pull/1078","repositories":[{"url":"https://github.com/kumahq/kuma","primary":true}],"summary":{"business_use_case":"It is becoming more important then ever to ensure that traffic is secure, observable, and reliable. Kuma service mesh enables users to adopt a zero trust application networking model while providing flexible traffic management and observability capabilities.  Kuma also supports a wide variety of platforms including Kubernetes, Nomad, Docker, and Virtual Machines. Thereby allowing organizations to take advantage of these benefits even at the start of their digital transformation journey.","integrations":"Flagger","personas":["SREs","DevOps","Platform Engineers","Architects","Developers"],"release_rate":"Every 8-10 weeks","tags":["mTLS","security","traffic management","observability","microservices","resilience","load balancing","service mesh","policy","wasm","zero trust","multi-cluster","cross-platform","kubernetes","virtual machines"],"use_case":"Kuma is a service mesh that combines the extensibility and performance of Envoy proxy with great UX and a powerful, yet flexible set of policies. It was built from the ground up to support Kubernetes, Docker, and VM environments seamlessly in a single deployment."},"tag":["network"],"twitter_url":"https://twitter.com/KumaMesh"},{"category":"Orchestration & Management","homepage_url":"https://linkerd.io/","id":"orchestration-management--service-mesh--linkerd","logo":"logos/f1940543e59719e7ce1929d7bf6004b9fc56db3a6a59a2dc6f0db16c789b28ac.svg","name":"Linkerd","subcategory":"Service Mesh","website":"https://linkerd.io/","accepted_at":"2017-01-23","artwork_url":"https://github.com/cncf/artwork/blob/master/examples/graduated.md#linkerd-logos","audits":[{"date":"2019-06-01","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/linkerd/linkerd2/blob/main/audits/2019/SECURITY_AUDIT.pdf","vendor":"Cure53"},{"date":"2020-06-05","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/ctz/rustls/blob/main/audit/TLS-01-report.pdf","vendor":"Cure53"},{"date":"2022-06-28","type":"security","url":"https://github.com/linkerd/li